The paper deals with the problem of graph clustering, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in various fields such as machine learning, computer vision, and network analysis. The use of lifted multicuts to represent clusterings is a recent development in this area, and the paper focuses on analyzing and optimizing these representations. This makes the paper relevant to several sub-categories of arXiv CS, including cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Among these, cs.DM and cs.DS are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with mathematical properties of graph decompositions and optimization algorithms. However, the paper also discusses applications of lifted multicuts in machine learning and computer vision, which makes cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV relevant categories as well.
